race.comment: CUBAN WATERS (8) returns off a dominant trial win and looks to have come back in terrific order. She tackled tougher company last campaign without breaking through, so this easier assignment should suit perfectly. Expect a bright return. YES I BELIEVE (4) mixed his form last prep but his peaks measure right up. Readied with two quiet trials and Holder sticks from the latest. He can make his presence felt fresh. PULAMBI (9) has been below her best in her last two but was ticking along nicely prior. Sent back to the jumpouts between runs and looks to have sharpened up. With Toeroek aboard from a good draw, she reads well. BRISEIS ECLIPSE (6) was a barnstorming winner first-up before struggling at Geelong in testing conditions third-up. Drops back to a winning trip and drawn to get all favours with Pannell. She's worth another chance. REAL VALENTIA (2) showed grit to score at Clare last time. Tougher here with more weight and another wide draw, but he deserves respect.
